adjectives.description: resistless (comparative more resistless, superlative most resistless)

entries.meaning: That cannot be resisted; irresistible. [from 16th c.]
examples: Delving earth in his resistless way, / Howling, the Child with fierce flames / Issu'd from Enitharmon.

entries.meaning: Putting up no resistance; unresisting. [from 16th c.]
examples: All this time they were doing something—I could not see what—to the corpse; sometimes they were too busy rifling the dead body, I believe, to talk; again they let it fall with a heavy, resistless thud, and took to quarrelling.
